column5: Driver mistakes the Ashbridges Bay boat launch for a "driveway of some sort."  I think everybody was okay.  https://www.cp24.com/news/motorist-drives-volkswagen-straight-into-water-at-ashbridges-bay-police-1.3986299
Too bad it wasn't an original VW Beetle, they would float for a while.
Going down hill , no road ahead and only water. This is NOT a sub and we don’t have a prop!  let’s keep going and finish our smoke?
But the GPS said...and to wonder how in hell did the driver get a licence.
Perhaps things have changed, but I was never tested on boat launches when I got my license.
Me neither, but back in the day we had common sense beaten into us.
Oh look, a baby Trumpeter swan.
sorry but people like this should not be allowed behind the wheel of a motor vehicle. could have killed someone.
funny! the article doesn't say if the driver was checked for alcohol or drugs ??
They did a brain scan but didn't find anything!!
Apparently the brain scan did actually find something!
